FeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qgc1665702595858.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qgc1665702595858.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qgc1665702595858.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qgc1665702595858\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__show_239722\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Display or refresh a form component, synchronizing the display and updating field and property values.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__topic_d77258e1_d77259e1_d77260e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__p_d77261e1_d77262e1_d77263e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">show</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__topic_d50802e1_d50803e1_d50804e1_d50805e1_d50806e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d90873e65\">Return Values </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__table_d7418e1_d7419e1_d7420e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values Commonly Returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> following\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">show</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__table_d7418e1_d7419e1_d7420e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__table_d7418e1_d7419e1_d7420e1__entry__2\">\n Error constant\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__table_d7418e1_d7419e1_d7420e1__entry__3\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qgc1665702595858__table_d7418e1_d7419e1_d7420e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1402</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qgc1665702595858__table_d7418e1_d7419e1_d7420e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_STATEMENT&gt;</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qgc1665702595858__table_d7418e1_d7419e1_d7420e1__entry__3\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">show</span> used in service component.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__topic_d50807e1_d50808e1_d50809e1_d50810e1_d50811e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d90873e129\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__d5909e20\">Use in Form components.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__topic_d50812e1_d50813e1_d50814e1_d50815e1_d50816e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d90873e138\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__p_d77276e1_d77277e1_d77278e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">show</span> statement displays a form component. All current field values are displayed and current property values are applied (with the exception of entity properties that refer to the current occurrence). No triggers are fired.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__p_d77279e1_d77280e1_d77281e1\">Unlike the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">edit</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">display</span> statements, which wait for user input, code execution continues after the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">show</span> statement, without waiting for user input.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__p_d77282e1_d77283e1_d77284e1\">In some situations, Uniface may not update the display completely when using a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">show</span> statement. This can be changed with the setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">AsynchGui</span> in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>. When set to 2 (Flush), the screen will be updated.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__section_lxj_q2m_zbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d90873e175\">Example: Redisplaying Values as They are Updated</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example shows the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">show</span> statement\n               being used to redisplay values in a form as they are updated (that is, while\n               processing continues):</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"qgc1665702595858__pre_pqw_q2m_zbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">function CountDown()\nvariables\n numeric j\nendvariables\nMyField.MyEnt = 10\nwhile (MyField.MyEnt &gt; 0)\n show\n j = 10000\n while (j&gt;0)\n j = j - 1\n endwhile\n MyField.MyEnt = MyField.MyEnt - 1\nendwhile\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gwk1665702595783.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>edit</a><p>Display the component in preparation for user input.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iqk1665702595933.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$editmode</a><p>Return or set a value that determines the degree to which a user can change data on the form component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/epe1665702596013.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$interactive</a><p>Return a boolean value indicating whether the current Form component is in interactive state.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615398\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615398\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "show Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Display or refresh a form component, synchronizing the display and updating field and property values. show Return Values Table 1. Values Commonly Returned in $procerror following show Value Error constant Meaning -1402 <UPROCERR_STATEMENT> show used in service component. Use Use in Form components. Description The show statement displays a form component. All current field values are displayed and current property values are applied (with the exception of entity properties that refer to the current occurrence). No triggers are fired. Unlike the edit and display statements, which wait for user input, code execution continues after the show statement, without waiting for user input. In some situations, Uniface may not update the display completely when using a show statement. This can be changed with the setting AsynchGui in the usys.ini . When set to 2 (Flush), the screen will be updated. Example: Redisplaying Values as They are Updated The following example shows the show statement being used to redisplay values in a form as they are updated (that is, while processing continues): function CountDown() variables numeric j endvariables MyField.MyEnt = 10 while (MyField.MyEnt > 0) show j = 10000 while (j>0) j = j - 1 endwhile MyField.MyEnt = MyField.MyEnt - 1 endwhile Copy Related Links edit Display the component in preparation for user input. $editmode Return or set a value that determines the degree to which a user can change data on the form component. $interactive Return a boolean value indicating whether the current Form component is in interactive state. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}